0. prerequisite
  ruby 1.8 (includng gem)
  postgesql
  postgis
  
and following gems
  rake
  rails
  GeoRuby
  mislav-will_paginate
  pg (or any postgresql driver module)
  mongrel(optional)
1. create database and install postgis functions.

 % createdb walkdb -E utf8
 % createlang -d walkdb plpgsql
 % psql walkdb -f lwpostgis.sql
 % psql walkdb -f spatial_ref_sys.sql

2. setup config files

 % cp config/config.rb.sample config/config.rb
 % vi config/config.rb
...
 % cp config/database.yml.sample config/database.yml
 % vi config/database.yml
...

3. install plugins
 % ./script/plugin install svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/georuby/SpatialAdapter/trunk/spatial_adapter
 % ./script/plugin install http://ennerchi.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/plugins/jrails

4. migrate db schemas
 % rake db:migrate

5. setup areas table
 in case of using japan.shp, visit http://www.esrij.com/products/gis_data/japanshp/japanshp.html and download zip file japan_ver62.zip. then extract japan_ver62.shp to a working directory.
 
 % shp2pgsql japan_ver62.shp -s 4326 -g the_geom -I  areas -W sjis > areas.sql
 % psql walkdb -f areas.sql

6. start server

 % ./script/server

